original_title: The Velvet Underground - Velvet Redux Live MCMXCIII
overview: Seminal experimental rock band The Velvet Underground, who initially disbanded in 1970, perform a set at L'Olympia in Paris, France in June 1993, during their brief reunion tour. The set features original founding members Lou Reed, John Cale, Sterling Morrison and Maureen Tucker performing 15 songs, including a new, previously unreleased track, "Coyote."
title: The Velvet Underground - Velvet Redux Live MCMXCIII
